headline: Royal Caribbean (RCL) Profit Margin Surges, Challenging Concerns Over Valuation and Growth Narratives
summary: Royal Caribbean Cruises (RCL) saw its net profit margins reach 23.3%, climbing from 16.2% a year ago, marking a notable expansion in profitability. Over the past five years, the company has turned profitable and grown earnings at an impressive 67.4% annual rate. However, this year's 56.3% growth lags that pace, pointing to some moderation. Looking ahead, annual earnings growth is forecast at 12.1%, trailing both the broader US market and hospitality sector averages. Its P/E ratio of 18.8x...
